const QUESTIONS = [
{"id":1,"cat":"品詞","q":"The marketing team's ___ to detail was evident in the flawless execution of the product launch campaign.","c":["attentive","attend","attention","attentively"],"a":2,"exp":"所有格 team's の後ろ+前置詞 to の前なので名詞 attention が正解。attention to detail「細部への配慮」は頻出コロケーション。(A)は形容詞、(C)は副詞、(D)は動詞。"},
{"id":2,"cat":"品詞","q":"Ms. Alvarez reviewed the proposal ___ before forwarding it to the board for final approval.","c":["thorough","thoroughness","more thorough","thoroughly"],"a":3,"exp":"reviewed the proposal で文が完成しており、動詞を修飾する副詞 thoroughly「徹底的に」が入る。動詞+目的語の後ろの空所は副詞が定石。"},
{"id":3,"cat":"語彙","q":"The new software update is expected to ___ the risk of data breaches by encrypting all customer information.","c":["conceive","assemble","mitigate","prolong"],"a":2,"exp":"mitigate「(リスク・影響を)軽減する」が文意に合う。mitigate the risk は頻出。(B)conceive 思いつく、(C)prolong 長引かせる、(D)assemble 組み立てる。"},
{"id":4,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"___ the unexpected surge in demand, the factory managed to fulfill all orders before the holiday season.","c":["Nevertheless","Although","Even","Despite"],"a":3,"exp":"空所の後ろが名詞句 the unexpected surge なので前置詞 Despite が正解。(B)Although は接続詞でSVが必要、(C)Nevertheless は副詞、(D)Even は単独では文頭導入に使えない。"},
{"id":5,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"By the time the auditors arrive next month, the accounting department ___ all the financial records.","c":["has organized","will have organized","is organizing","organized"],"a":1,"exp":"By the time+未来の時点なので、未来のある時点までの完了を表す未来完了 will have organized が正解。by the time は完了形と相性が良い頻出パターン。"},
{"id":6,"cat":"品詞","q":"Employees who complete the certification program are eligible for a ___ salary increase.","c":["substance","substantiate","substantial","substantially"],"a":2,"exp":"冠詞 a と名詞 salary increase の間なので形容詞 substantial「大幅な」が入る。(B)は副詞、(C)は名詞、(D)は動詞「立証する」。"},
{"id":7,"cat":"語彙","q":"Please ___ from using mobile phones during the safety demonstration, as they may interfere with the equipment.","c":["prevent","refrain","prohibit","avoid"],"a":1,"exp":"refrain from -ing「〜を控える」。prevent/prohibit は prevent A from -ing の形で目的語が必要。avoid は前置詞 from を取らず avoid -ing となる。"},
{"id":8,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"The shipment will be delivered on schedule ___ the weather conditions remain favorable.","c":["regardless","provided that","owing to","in case of"],"a":1,"exp":"後ろにSV(the weather conditions remain)が続くので接続詞の働きをする provided that「〜という条件で」が正解。(B)(C)は前置詞句で名詞が続く。(D)は regardless of の形が必要。"},
{"id":9,"cat":"品詞","q":"The consultant's recommendations proved ___ in reducing the company's operational costs by nearly 20 percent.","c":["value","valuably","invaluable","valuation"],"a":2,"exp":"prove+形容詞「〜だと分かる」の形。invaluable は「非常に貴重な」という意味の形容詞(in- は否定ではない点に注意)。(A)(D)は名詞、(B)は副詞。"},
{"id":10,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The board of directors recommended that the merger agreement ___ before the end of the fiscal year.","c":["will be finalized","was finalized","be finalized","is finalized"],"a":2,"exp":"recommend/suggest/require などの後の that 節では動詞は原形(仮定法現在)。受動なので be finalized が正解。主語が三人称単数でも s は付かない。"},
{"id":11,"cat":"語彙","q":"The two companies reached a ___ agreement that allows both parties to share manufacturing facilities.","c":["spacious","punctual","gradual","mutual"],"a":3,"exp":"mutual agreement「相互の合意」が正しいコロケーション。(B)punctual 時間を守る、(C)spacious 広々とした、(D)gradual 段階的な。"},
{"id":12,"cat":"品詞","q":"All visitors must sign in at the front desk ___ entering the research facility.","c":["beforehand","previous","prior to","advance"],"a":2,"exp":"prior to -ing「〜する前に」。前置詞句 prior to の後ろには名詞・動名詞が続く。(B)は形容詞、(C)は副詞で目的語を取れない、(D)は in advance の形で使う。"},
{"id":13,"cat":"その他","q":"Applicants ___ résumés are received by Friday will be contacted for an interview next week.","c":["which","whom","whose","who"],"a":2,"exp":"空所の後ろの名詞 résumés との所有関係(応募者の履歴書)を表す所有格の関係代名詞 whose が正解。who/whom の後ろに無冠詞名詞+動詞は続かない。"},
{"id":14,"cat":"語彙","q":"The hotel offers a complimentary shuttle service to the airport at 30-minute ___ throughout the day.","c":["intervals","durations","extents","frequencies"],"a":0,"exp":"at ~ intervals「〜間隔で」が定型表現。(B)duration は継続時間、(C)frequency は頻度、(D)extent は程度で、いずれも at 30-minute ___ の形に合わない。"},
{"id":15,"cat":"品詞","q":"The newly appointed CEO outlined her vision with such ___ that even skeptical investors were persuaded.","c":["clearly","clarity","clear","clarify"],"a":1,"exp":"such+名詞の形。前置詞 with の目的語でもあるので名詞 clarity「明快さ」が正解。with clarity = clearly。"},
{"id":16,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"___ its compact size, the new printer can handle high-volume printing jobs more efficiently than larger models.","c":["Whereas","Given","Unless","Despite"],"a":3,"exp":"「小型にもかかわらず大量印刷を処理できる」という譲歩の文脈なので前置詞 Despite が正解。(A)Given「〜を考慮すると」では逆の意味になる。(C)(D)は接続詞。"},
{"id":17,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"Had the maintenance crew inspected the equipment earlier, the production delay ___ avoided.","c":["can be","will be","could have been","was"],"a":2,"exp":"Had the crew inspected は If the crew had inspected の倒置(仮定法過去完了)。帰結節は could/would have+過去分詞となるため could have been avoided が正解。"},
{"id":18,"cat":"語彙","q":"Sales representatives are required to submit their expense reports ___ to the regional manager by the fifth of each month.","c":["closely","fairly","directly","shortly"],"a":2,"exp":"submit ~ directly to ...「〜に直接提出する」。(B)shortly まもなく、(C)fairly かなり、(D)closely 綿密に、はいずれも to 以下と自然につながらない。"},
{"id":19,"cat":"品詞","q":"The seminar on effective negotiation was so ___ that the organizers decided to offer it again next quarter.","c":["informative","information","inform","informatively"],"a":0,"exp":"so+形容詞+that 構文。主語 the seminar の補語になる形容詞 informative「有益な」が正解。人ではなく物が主語なので -ive 形。"},
{"id":20,"cat":"その他","q":"Of the three proposals submitted, the design by Kimura Associates was judged the ___ feasible.","c":["more","most","very","much"],"a":1,"exp":"Of the three「3つの中で」とあるので最上級 the most feasible が正解。2つの比較なら the more だが、3つ以上は最上級。"},
{"id":21,"cat":"語彙","q":"The R&D division was allocated ___ funding to accelerate the development of the prototype.","c":["additional","multiple","numerous","plenty"],"a":0,"exp":"funding は不可算名詞なので additional「追加の」が正解。(B)numerous と(C)multiple は可算名詞の複数形に付く。(D)plenty は plenty of の形が必要。"},
{"id":22,"cat":"品詞","q":"Ms. Chen has been recognized ___ for her contributions to sustainable packaging design.","c":["repetitive","repeatedly","repetition","repeat"],"a":1,"exp":"has been recognized という受動態の動詞を修飾する副詞 repeatedly「繰り返し」が正解。受動態の間や後ろの空所は副詞が入ることが多い。"},
{"id":23,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"The warranty covers all repair costs ___ the damage results from normal use of the product.","c":["in spite of","as long as","instead of","as well as"],"a":1,"exp":"後ろにSVが続き「通常使用による損傷である限り」という条件を表すので接続詞 as long as が正解。(B)(C)(D)はいずれも前置詞的で名詞が続く。"},
{"id":24,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The quarterly report, together with the budget projections, ___ to be submitted by noon tomorrow.","c":["needs","needing","need","are needing"],"a":0,"exp":"主語は単数の the quarterly report。together with 以下は修飾句で動詞の数に影響しない。よって三単現の needs が正解。挿入句による主述一致のひっかけ問題。"},
{"id":25,"cat":"語彙","q":"Due to a scheduling conflict, the keynote speech has been ___ until the second day of the conference.","c":["canceled","withdrawn","expired","postponed"],"a":3,"exp":"until があるので「2日目まで延期された」postponed が正解。(B)canceled 中止(until と矛盾)、(C)withdrawn 撤回、(D)expired 期限切れ。"},
{"id":26,"cat":"品詞","q":"The ___ of the merger negotiations remains strictly confidential until both boards reach a final decision.","c":["outcome","come out","outcoming","outcomes are"],"a":0,"exp":"The ___ of ~ remains と続くので、単数扱いの名詞 outcome「結果」が正解。remains が三単現である点も手がかり。"},
{"id":27,"cat":"語彙","q":"Employees may ___ up to three days of unused vacation time to the following year.","c":["put off","carry over","turn down","take after"],"a":1,"exp":"carry over「(休暇などを)繰り越す」が正解。(B)take after 似ている、(C)put off 延期する、(D)turn down 断る。句動詞の意味を問う頻出パターン。"},
{"id":28,"cat":"品詞","q":"To remain ___ in the global market, the company invests heavily in employee training programs.","c":["compete","competitive","competition","competitively"],"a":1,"exp":"remain+形容詞「〜のままである」。competitive「競争力のある」が正解。remain/stay/become などの後ろは補語の形容詞。"},
{"id":29,"cat":"その他","q":"Neither the sales manager ___ her assistants were able to attend the trade show in Osaka.","c":["or","and","nor","but"],"a":2,"exp":"neither A nor B「AもBも〜ない」の相関接続詞。neither とペアになるのは nor のみ。"},
{"id":30,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"The renovation of the lobby is expected to be completed ___ the end of March.","c":["in","until","on","by"],"a":3,"exp":"「3月末までに完了する」という期限を表すのは by。until は「〜まで(継続)」で、complete のような一回で終わる動作には使えない。by と until の使い分けは頻出。"},
{"id":31,"cat":"語彙","q":"The customer service department strives to respond to all inquiries in a ___ manner.","c":["promptly","timely","punctually","shortly"],"a":1,"exp":"in a timely manner「速やかに」が定型表現。timely は -ly で終わるが形容詞なので manner を修飾できる。(B)(C)(D)は副詞で名詞を修飾できない。"},
{"id":32,"cat":"品詞","q":"Ticket holders will receive a full refund if the concert is canceled due to ___ circumstances.","c":["foreseeing","foresee","unforeseen","unforeseeably"],"a":2,"exp":"名詞 circumstances を修飾する形容詞 unforeseen「予期せぬ」が正解。unforeseen circumstances は頻出コロケーション。"},
{"id":33,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The technicians ___ the network servers when the power outage occurred last night.","c":["have upgraded","were upgrading","upgrade","upgraded"],"a":1,"exp":"when 以下の過去の一時点に「〜している最中だった」ので過去進行形 were upgrading が正解。過去の動作の途中を表す典型パターン。"},
{"id":34,"cat":"語彙","q":"The award ceremony will ___ with a dinner reception in the grand ballroom.","c":["conclude","achieve","terminate","finalize"],"a":0,"exp":"conclude with ~「〜で締めくくられる」。自動詞用法があるのは conclude。(C)terminate も終わるだが with との組み合わせで祝宴の文脈に合わない。(B)(D)は他動詞で目的語が必要。"},
{"id":35,"cat":"品詞","q":"Because of its ___ location near two major highways, the warehouse is ideal for distribution operations.","c":["strategize","strategic","strategy","strategically"],"a":1,"exp":"所有格 its と名詞 location の間なので形容詞 strategic「戦略的な」が正解。(A)は副詞、(C)は名詞、(D)は動詞。"},
{"id":36,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"___ the two candidates were equally qualified, the hiring committee based its decision on the interview results.","c":["During","Regarding","Since","Despite of"],"a":2,"exp":"後ろにSVが続き「同等の資格だったので」という理由を表す接続詞 Since が正解。(B)(D)は前置詞。(C)Despite of という形は存在しない(Despite または In spite of)。"},
{"id":37,"cat":"語彙","q":"The finance director asked the team to ___ the budget figures before the presentation to shareholders.","c":["testify","verify","notify","qualify"],"a":1,"exp":"verify「(数字・事実を)検証する、確認する」が正解。(B)testify 証言する、(C)notify 通知する(人が目的語)、(D)qualify 資格を与える。-ify で終わる動詞の意味の識別。"},
{"id":38,"cat":"品詞","q":"Attendance at the annual shareholders' meeting was ___ higher than in previous years.","c":["consider","considerably","considerable","consideration"],"a":1,"exp":"比較級 higher を修飾する副詞 considerably「かなり」が正解。比較級の前の空所には much/far/considerably/significantly などの副詞が入る。"},
{"id":39,"cat":"その他","q":"The company's new headquarters is twice ___ the previous building, with space for over 2,000 employees.","c":["the biggest","bigger","the size of","as big"],"a":2,"exp":"twice the size of ~「〜の2倍の大きさ」が定型。twice as big as ~ も可だが (B) は as が1つ欠けている。倍数表現の頻出形。"},
{"id":40,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"All employees are encouraged ___ the wellness workshop scheduled for next Thursday.","c":["to attend","attended","attend","attending"],"a":0,"exp":"encourage A to do の受動態 be encouraged to do「〜するよう奨励される」。to 不定詞を取る動詞の受動態パターン。"},
{"id":41,"cat":"語彙","q":"The lease agreement clearly ___ that tenants are responsible for minor repairs and maintenance.","c":["allocates","stipulates","designates","nominates"],"a":1,"exp":"stipulate that ~「〜と(契約書などが)規定する」が正解。(B)designate 指定する、(C)nominate 指名する、(D)allocate 割り当てる、は that 節を取らない。"},
{"id":42,"cat":"品詞","q":"The museum's newest exhibition has attracted a ___ number of international visitors this summer.","c":["recording","records","recorded","record"],"a":3,"exp":"a record number of ~「記録的な数の〜」が定型表現。record が名詞のまま形容詞的に number を修飾する。(B)recorded「録音された」では意味が通らない。"},
{"id":43,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"Passengers should keep their boarding passes accessible ___ the duration of the flight.","c":["during","while","for","throughout"],"a":3,"exp":"throughout the duration of ~「〜の間ずっと」。throughout は期間全体にわたる継続を強調する。(B)while は接続詞。for/during も期間に使うが、duration との組み合わせでは throughout が最も自然。"},
{"id":44,"cat":"語彙","q":"After months of negotiation, the union and management finally reached a ___ on the new wage structure.","c":["consensus","boundary","dilemma","tribute"],"a":0,"exp":"reach a consensus「合意に達する」が定型コロケーション。(B)dilemma ジレンマ、(C)boundary 境界、(D)tribute 賛辞。"},
{"id":45,"cat":"品詞","q":"Ms. Okafor is widely regarded as one of the most ___ financial analysts in the industry.","c":["accomplish","accomplishment","accomplished","accomplishing"],"a":2,"exp":"most の後ろで名詞 analysts を修飾する形容詞 accomplished「熟達した」が正解。過去分詞由来の形容詞。(C)accomplishing では「達成しつつある」となり不自然。"},
{"id":46,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The new security protocol requires that every visitor ___ a photo ID at the reception desk.","c":["present","presented","presenting","presents"],"a":0,"exp":"require that 節内は動詞の原形(仮定法現在)。visitor は三人称単数だが present に s は付かない。recommend/suggest/insist/require の that 節は原形が鉄則。"},
{"id":47,"cat":"語彙","q":"The airline offers ___ rates for corporate clients who book more than 50 flights per year.","c":["preferential","preferring","preferred","preferable"],"a":0,"exp":"preferential rates「優遇料金」が定型コロケーション。(B)preferable は「より望ましい」で人の好みを表し、(C)preferred は「好まれる」でどちらも料金体系の文脈に合わない。"},
{"id":48,"cat":"その他","q":"Employees may park in the visitor lot only if ___ own designated spaces are unavailable.","c":["their","them","theirs","they"],"a":0,"exp":"後ろの名詞句 own designated spaces を修飾する所有格 their が正解。one's own+名詞の形。"},
{"id":49,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"___ receipt of your payment, we will ship your order within two business days.","c":["While","Upon","Until","Once"],"a":1,"exp":"upon receipt of ~「〜を受領次第」が定型表現。upon+名詞で「〜するとすぐに」。(C)Once は接続詞でSVが必要。"},
{"id":50,"cat":"語彙","q":"The training manual provides ___ instructions on how to operate the new inventory system.","c":["spacious","widespread","extensive knowledge","comprehensive"],"a":3,"exp":"comprehensive instructions「包括的な説明」が自然なコロケーション。(C)widespread は「(現象などが)広範囲に広がった」で instructions を修飾しない。(D)spacious は空間の広さ。"},
{"id":51,"cat":"品詞","q":"The committee praised the intern for her ___ in resolving the scheduling conflict without managerial assistance.","c":["resource","resourcefully","resourceful","resourcefulness"],"a":3,"exp":"所有格 her の後ろ+前置詞 in の前なので名詞が入る。resourcefulness「機転、臨機応変さ」が正解。(D)resource「資源」では意味が通らない。抽象名詞を選ぶやや難問。"},
{"id":52,"cat":"語彙","q":"Construction of the new terminal is ___ ahead of schedule, thanks to favorable weather conditions.","c":["processing","preceding","proceeding","prevailing"],"a":2,"exp":"proceed「進行する」(自動詞)が正解。(B)process は他動詞「処理する」、(C)precede「〜に先行する」、(D)prevail「普及する、勝る」。スペルが似た動詞の識別問題。"},
{"id":53,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"The office will remain open during the renovation, ___ noise levels may occasionally be disruptive.","c":["despite","because of","in order that","although"],"a":3,"exp":"「営業は続けるが騒音があるかもしれない」という譲歩の関係。後ろにSVが続くので接続詞 although が正解。(B)(C)は前置詞。(D)in order that は目的を表し文意に合わない。"},
{"id":54,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"Once the contract ___ by both parties, work on the project can officially begin.","c":["has been signed","is signing","signed","will be signed"],"a":0,"exp":"時・条件の副詞節(Once ~)では未来のことでも現在形・現在完了形を使う。受動の意味なので has been signed が正解。(A)will be signed は副詞節内なので不可。"},
{"id":55,"cat":"品詞","q":"Despite the ___ of the instructions, several customers contacted the help desk for assistance.","c":["simply","simplicity","simplify","simple"],"a":1,"exp":"前置詞 Despite の目的語+冠詞 the の後ろなので名詞 simplicity「簡潔さ」が正解。「説明書は簡単だったのに問い合わせが来た」という文意。"},
{"id":56,"cat":"語彙","q":"The hotel's location is ___ to both the convention center and the historic district.","c":["comfortable","appropriate","suitable","convenient"],"a":3,"exp":"convenient to/for ~「〜に便利な(近い)」。場所のアクセスの良さは convenient。(B)comfortable は快適さ、(C)(D)は「適切な」で to 以下との組み合わせが不自然。"},
{"id":57,"cat":"品詞","q":"The auditors examined the financial statements ___ submitted by the accounting department last week.","c":["originally","original","origin","originality"],"a":0,"exp":"過去分詞 submitted を修飾する副詞 originally「元々、最初に」が正解。分詞の前の空所は副詞。"},
{"id":58,"cat":"その他","q":"___ wishing to participate in the company retreat should register with Human Resources by Friday.","c":["They","Anyone who","Whoever","Those"],"a":3,"exp":"Those wishing to do「〜したい人々」= Those who wish to do の分詞短縮形。(C)Whoever と(D)Anyone who の後ろには動詞(wishes)が必要で、wishing とはつながらない。"},
{"id":59,"cat":"語彙","q":"The keynote speaker gave a ___ account of how the company overcame its early financial difficulties.","c":["insistent","compelling","forceful","persuadable"],"a":1,"exp":"compelling「(話が)引き込まれる、説得力のある」が正解。a compelling account/story は頻出。(B)persuadable は「説得されやすい」で逆方向。(D)forceful は「force を伴う」ニュアンスで account に不自然。"},
{"id":60,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"All laboratory equipment must be sterilized ___ accordance with the safety guidelines.","c":["in","on","for","by"],"a":0,"exp":"in accordance with ~「〜に従って」が定型表現。前置詞のイディオムは丸ごと覚える必要がある頻出パターン。"},
{"id":61,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The marketing director suggested ___ the product launch until consumer testing is complete.","c":["delay","delayed","to delay","delaying"],"a":3,"exp":"suggest は動名詞を目的語に取る動詞(megafeps)。suggest doing「〜することを提案する」。to 不定詞は不可。"},
{"id":62,"cat":"品詞","q":"Renovation costs were ___ estimated at $2 million, but the final figure was considerably higher.","c":["initially","initial","initiate","initiative"],"a":0,"exp":"受動態 were estimated の間に入って動詞を修飾する副詞 initially「当初」が正解。be動詞と過去分詞の間の空所は副詞の定位置。"},
{"id":63,"cat":"語彙","q":"Under the new policy, expense reports lacking proper documentation will not be ___ for reimbursement.","c":["capable","entitled","permissible","eligible"],"a":3,"exp":"be eligible for ~「〜の対象となる資格がある」。(B)entitled は be entitled to、(C)capable は be capable of。前置詞との組み合わせで判断する語彙問題。"},
{"id":64,"cat":"品詞","q":"Mr. Danville responded to the customer's complaint in a ___ and professional manner.","c":["courteous","court","courteously","courtesy"],"a":0,"exp":"and で professional(形容詞)と並列され、名詞 manner を修飾するので形容詞 courteous「礼儀正しい」が正解。並列構造から品詞を判断する問題。"},
{"id":65,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"Refunds will be issued ___ 10 business days of receiving the returned merchandise.","c":["within","among","along","beyond"],"a":0,"exp":"within ~ days of -ing「〜してから…日以内に」が定型。返品・返金の文脈で極めて頻出の表現。"},
{"id":66,"cat":"語彙","q":"The IT department will ___ the old servers with energy-efficient models over the weekend.","c":["exchange","transfer","substitute","replace"],"a":3,"exp":"replace A with B「AをBに取り替える」。(B)substitute は substitute B for A の語順で意味が逆になる点に注意。with を手がかりに選ぶ。"},
{"id":67,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"___ for over three decades, the family-owned bakery has become a beloved neighborhood institution.","c":["To operate","Having operated","Operated","Operating"],"a":1,"exp":"「30年以上営業してきて(その結果)今や〜」という完了の意味を表す分詞構文 Having operated が正解。主節より前から続く動作には having+過去分詞。"},
{"id":68,"cat":"品詞","q":"The spreadsheet contains ___ data on regional sales trends over the past five years.","c":["analyze","analytical","analysis","analytically"],"a":1,"exp":"名詞 data を修飾する形容詞 analytical「分析的な」が正解。(D)analysis も名詞だが analysis data という複合名詞は不自然で、analytical data が自然。"},
{"id":69,"cat":"語彙","q":"Attendance at the optional training session was surprisingly high, ___ strong interest in the new software.","c":["featuring","expressing","indicating","informing"],"a":2,"exp":"indicating ~「〜を示しながら(示すものだった)」という分詞構文。事実・データが何かを「示す」は indicate。(C)inform は人が目的語。(B)express は感情を表に出す。"},
{"id":70,"cat":"その他","q":"The more thoroughly you prepare for the client meeting, ___ the negotiation is likely to proceed.","c":["the more smoothly","the smoothest","smoother","more smoothly"],"a":0,"exp":"The 比較級 ~, the 比較級 ...「〜すればするほど…」の構文。proceed(動詞)を修飾するので副詞の比較級 the more smoothly が正解。"},
{"id":71,"cat":"品詞","q":"Guests are asked to handle the antique furniture with extreme ___ during the estate tour.","c":["carefully","care","caring","careful"],"a":1,"exp":"前置詞 with+形容詞 extreme の後ろなので名詞 care が正解。with care = carefully。前置詞の目的語は名詞という基本パターン。"},
{"id":72,"cat":"語彙","q":"The proposed budget cuts will ___ affect the transportation and utilities departments.","c":["attentively","abundantly","adversely","expressively"],"a":2,"exp":"adversely affect「悪影響を及ぼす」が頻出コロケーション。(B)attentively 注意深く、(C)expressively 表情豊かに、(D)abundantly 豊富に。"},
{"id":73,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"___ demand for the limited-edition sneakers was so high, the retailer imposed a two-pair limit per customer.","c":["Due to","Owing to","Because","Because of"],"a":2,"exp":"後ろに demand was so high というSVが続くので接続詞 Because が正解。(B)(C)(D)はすべて前置詞句で名詞しか続けられない。"},
{"id":74,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The revised employee handbook ___ to all staff members by the end of this week.","c":["has distributed","will be distributed","is distributing","will distribute"],"a":1,"exp":"handbook は「配布される」側なので受動態 will be distributed が正解。主語と動詞の能動・受動関係を見極める頻出問題。"},
{"id":75,"cat":"語彙","q":"Dr. Yamamoto's research findings are highly ___ to the ongoing debate about renewable energy policy.","c":["preliminary","relevant","respective","tentative"],"a":1,"exp":"relevant to ~「〜に関連性が高い」。(B)respective それぞれの、(C)tentative 暫定的な、(D)preliminary 予備の。to との相性で判断。"},
{"id":76,"cat":"品詞","q":"___ of the merger was met with enthusiasm by shareholders of both companies.","c":["Announce","Announcing","Announced","Announcement"],"a":3,"exp":"文頭で主語になり、of の前に置ける名詞 Announcement が正解。動詞 was met の主語が必要。(D)Announcing だと動名詞で「発表すること」となり受動の was met with と不自然。"},
{"id":77,"cat":"語彙","q":"To avoid delays at the security checkpoint, please have your identification ___ available.","c":["precisely","readily","legibly","evenly"],"a":1,"exp":"readily available「すぐに利用できる、すぐ出せる」が定型コロケーション。(B)legibly 読みやすく、(C)precisely 正確に、(D)evenly 均等に。"},
{"id":78,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"The catering staff set up the banquet hall ___ the guests began arriving at seven o'clock.","c":["until","during","prior","by the time"],"a":3,"exp":"後ろにSV(the guests began)が続き「客が到着し始めるまでに」という意味なので接続詞 by the time が正解。(C)during は前置詞。(D)prior は prior to の形が必要。"},
{"id":79,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"Anyone ___ questions about the new benefits package should contact the human resources office.","c":["having","has","had","have"],"a":0,"exp":"Anyone who has の who has を分詞 having に短縮した形。Anyone having questions「質問がある人は誰でも」。名詞を後ろから修飾する現在分詞。"},
{"id":80,"cat":"語彙","q":"The board voted ___ to approve the expansion into Southeast Asian markets.","c":["mutually","unanimously","namely","collectively"],"a":1,"exp":"vote unanimously「全会一致で可決する」が定型コロケーション。(B)mutually 相互に、(C)collectively 集団で(意味は近いが vote との定型は unanimously)、(D)namely すなわち。"},
{"id":81,"cat":"品詞","q":"The workshop is designed to help managers communicate more ___ with their team members.","c":["effective","effectively","effectiveness","effect"],"a":1,"exp":"動詞 communicate を修飾する副詞 effectively が正解。more とセットで比較級を作っている。動詞の後ろの空所は副詞。"},
{"id":82,"cat":"その他","q":"Ms. Patel will interview the candidates ___ résumés most closely match the job requirements.","c":["which","whose","who","that"],"a":1,"exp":"「候補者の履歴書」という所有関係なので whose が正解。whose+名詞+動詞の語順を確認する。"},
{"id":83,"cat":"語彙","q":"The company's profits rose sharply last quarter, ___ analysts' expectations by a wide margin.","c":["exceeding","enlarging","expanding","raising"],"a":0,"exp":"exceed expectations「予想を上回る」が頻出コロケーション。分詞構文で「予想を大きく上回って」。(B)(C)は「拡大する」、(D)raise は「引き上げる」。"},
{"id":84,"cat":"品詞","q":"Employees should direct any ___ regarding payroll to the accounting department.","c":["inquiries","inquisitive","inquiring","inquire"],"a":0,"exp":"any の後ろで direct の目的語となる名詞 inquiries「問い合わせ」が正解。direct inquiries to ~「問い合わせを〜に回す」は頻出表現。"},
{"id":85,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"___ the survey results, most customers prefer the online ordering system to the mobile app.","c":["According to","As far as","Depending","Concerned"],"a":0,"exp":"according to ~「〜によると」。情報源を示す定番の前置詞句。(B)Depending は depending on の形が必要。(C)As far as は接続詞的でSVが続く。"},
{"id":86,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"If the shipment ___ on time, the assembly line would not have been idle for two days.","c":["arrived","arrives","would arrive","had arrived"],"a":3,"exp":"帰結節が would not have been(仮定法過去完了)なので、if 節は had+過去分詞。過去の事実に反する仮定「もし届いていたら」。"},
{"id":87,"cat":"語彙","q":"Please review the attached document and ___ us of any errors by Wednesday.","c":["announce","mention","notify","reveal"],"a":2,"exp":"notify A of B「AにBを知らせる」。人を目的語に取り of と結びつくのは notify。(B)announce や(D)reveal は人を直接目的語に取らない。"},
{"id":88,"cat":"品詞","q":"The device's battery life is ___ superior to that of competing products in the same price range.","c":["noticeable","noticing","notice","noticeably"],"a":3,"exp":"形容詞 superior を修飾する副詞 noticeably「著しく」が正解。形容詞の前の空所は副詞。"},
{"id":89,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"Neither of the printers is working properly; ___, all documents must be sent to the third-floor copy center.","c":["nonetheless","similarly","otherwise","consequently"],"a":3,"exp":"「プリンターが故障している。その結果〜」という因果関係を表す接続副詞 consequently が正解。(B)otherwise さもなければ、(C)nonetheless それにもかかわらず、(D)similarly 同様に。"},
{"id":90,"cat":"語彙","q":"The seminar will cover strategies for ___ long-term relationships with corporate clients.","c":["assembling","cultivating","enrolling","germinating"],"a":1,"exp":"cultivate a relationship「関係を築く、育む」が定型コロケーション。cultivate は畑を耕す→関係・skill を育てるの比喩で頻出。(B)germinate は種が発芽する。"},
{"id":91,"cat":"品詞","q":"___, the restaurant's head chef trained at a prestigious culinary institute in Lyon.","c":["Impressively","Impression","Impressive","Impress"],"a":0,"exp":"文全体を修飾する文頭の副詞 Impressively「見事なことに」が正解。カンマで区切られた文頭の空所は副詞が定石。"},
{"id":92,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The facilities manager insists that the ventilation system ___ inspected twice a year.","c":["will be","was","be","is"],"a":2,"exp":"insist that 節内は動詞の原形(仮定法現在)。受動なので be inspected。insist/demand/require/recommend の that 節は原形。"},
{"id":93,"cat":"語彙","q":"Due to ___ circumstances, tonight's outdoor screening has been moved to the community hall.","c":["unspoken","unintended","unforeseen","unlimited"],"a":2,"exp":"unforeseen circumstances「予期せぬ事情」が定型表現。(B)unintended 意図しない、(C)unspoken 暗黙の、(D)unlimited 無制限の。"},
{"id":94,"cat":"その他","q":"Each of the conference rooms ___ equipped with a projector and a video conferencing system.","c":["are","is","were","being"],"a":1,"exp":"each of+複数名詞は単数扱いなので is が正解。each/every/either は常に単数扱い。主述一致の頻出ひっかけ。"},
{"id":95,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"The fitness center is open to all residents ___ charge as part of the building's amenity package.","c":["in terms of","on behalf of","free of","instead of"],"a":2,"exp":"free of charge「無料で」が定型表現。(C)in terms of 〜の観点で、(D)on behalf of 〜を代表して。"},
{"id":96,"cat":"語彙","q":"The legal team advised the company to ___ caution when drafting the joint venture agreement.","c":["perform","exercise","operate","conduct"],"a":1,"exp":"exercise caution「注意を払う」が定型コロケーション。exercise は「(権利・注意などを)行使する」の意味で頻出。perform/conduct は業務・調査と結びつく。"},
{"id":97,"cat":"品詞","q":"The hotel underwent an ___ renovation that took nearly eighteen months to complete.","c":["extend","extension","extensive","extensively"],"a":2,"exp":"冠詞 an と名詞 renovation の間なので形容詞 extensive「大規模な」が正解。extensive renovation は頻出コロケーション。"},
{"id":98,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"By next April, Ms. Rowe ___ for the firm for twenty-five years.","c":["will work","will have worked","has worked","worked"],"a":1,"exp":"By next April という未来の時点までの継続を表すので未来完了 will have worked が正解。「来年4月で勤続25年になる」。"},
{"id":99,"cat":"語彙","q":"Customer feedback plays an ___ role in shaping the company's product development strategy.","c":["entire","integral","overall","utter"],"a":1,"exp":"play an integral role「不可欠な役割を果たす」が定型。(B)entire は「全体の」で role と組み合わせない。(C)utter は「完全な(悪い意味が多い)」。"},
{"id":100,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"___ signing the lease, tenants should carefully inspect the property for existing damage.","c":["Formerly","Previously","Ahead","Before"],"a":3,"exp":"Before -ing「〜する前に」。前置詞として動名詞を取れるのは Before。(B)Ahead は ahead of の形が必要。(C)(D)は副詞で目的語を取れない。"},
{"id":101,"cat":"品詞","q":"The spa's ___ atmosphere makes it a popular destination for guests seeking relaxation.","c":["tranquilly","tranquility","tranquil","tranquilize"],"a":2,"exp":"所有格 The spa's と名詞 atmosphere の間なので形容詞 tranquil「静かな、穏やかな」が正解。(B)は名詞、(C)は副詞、(D)は動詞。"},
{"id":102,"cat":"語彙","q":"The merger is still ___ regulatory approval and is expected to close by year's end.","c":["pending","waiting","holding","remaining"],"a":0,"exp":"pending「〜を待つ間の、〜次第の」が前置詞的に使われる形。pending regulatory approval「規制当局の承認待ちで」。(B)waiting は waiting for が必要。"},
{"id":103,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"Employees may work remotely twice a week ___ they maintain consistent productivity levels.","c":["despite","except","during","provided"],"a":3,"exp":"provided (that) SV「〜という条件で」。後ろにSVが続くので接続詞の働きをする provided が正解。条件を表す接続詞の頻出パターン。"},
{"id":104,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The award-winning documentary ___ in over forty countries since its release last spring.","c":["has been shown","showed","was shown","is showing"],"a":0,"exp":"since its release「公開以来」があるので現在完了。documentary は「上映される」側なので受動の has been shown が正解。since は現在完了のシグナル。"},
{"id":105,"cat":"品詞","q":"Mr. Osei reviewed the vendor contracts with great ___ before recommending any changes.","c":["diligent","diligently","diligentness","diligence"],"a":3,"exp":"with great+名詞の形。diligence「勤勉さ、入念さ」が正解。with diligence = diligently。(D)diligentness という語は存在しない。"},
{"id":106,"cat":"語彙","q":"The city council approved a ___ to widen the main road leading to the industrial park.","c":["suggestion box","statement","preference","proposal"],"a":3,"exp":"approve a proposal「提案を承認する」が自然。道路拡張のような公共事業の計画は proposal。(C)preference 好み、(D)statement 声明。"},
{"id":107,"cat":"品詞","q":"The technical support team resolved the server issue far more ___ than management had anticipated.","c":["quickly","quicker","quick","quickness"],"a":0,"exp":"動詞 resolved を修飾するので副詞 quickly。more quickly than で比較級を作っている。(B)quicker は形容詞の比較級で動詞を修飾できない。"},
{"id":108,"cat":"その他","q":"___ attended last year's leadership summit found the networking sessions particularly valuable.","c":["Which","Anyone","Those who","Whoever"],"a":2,"exp":"Those who+動詞「〜した人々」。attended と found の2つの動詞があるため、主語になれて節を導く Those who が正解。(B)Whoever も文法上可能に見えるが「誰でも」の意味で全員が価値を見出した文意には Those who が適切。(C)Anyone は who が必要。"},
{"id":109,"cat":"語彙","q":"Prices listed in the catalog are subject to ___ without prior notice.","c":["change","transition","variety","exchange"],"a":0,"exp":"be subject to change「変更される可能性がある」が定型表現。without prior notice「予告なしに」とセットで頻出。"},
{"id":110,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"___ of the two locations offers sufficient parking, so the event will be held at the convention center instead.","c":["Both","Neither","Either","None"],"a":1,"exp":"of the two「2つのうち」+「その代わりに別会場で」という文意から、2者の否定 Neither が正解。(B)None は3つ以上の否定。(C)Both だと so 以下と矛盾。"},
{"id":111,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The company president was seen ___ the new factory site with a group of foreign investors.","c":["to touring","touring","tour","toured"],"a":1,"exp":"see A doing の受動態 be seen doing「〜しているところを見られる」。was seen touring が正解。知覚動詞の受動態では to 不定詞(be seen to do)も可だが選択肢にないため touring。"},
{"id":112,"cat":"語彙","q":"The restaurant has earned a reputation for its ___ service and innovative menu.","c":["exempt","executive","exceptional","excessive"],"a":2,"exp":"exceptional service「格別のサービス」が正解。(B)excessive「過剰な」はネガティブ。(C)exempt「免除された」。ex- で始まる紛らわしい語の識別。"},
{"id":113,"cat":"品詞","q":"Please ensure that all packages are labeled ___ before they are transferred to the loading dock.","c":["correctly","correct","correction","corrected"],"a":0,"exp":"are labeled という受動態の後ろで動詞を修飾する副詞 correctly が正解。label A correctly「正しくラベルを貼る」の受動形。"},
{"id":114,"cat":"語彙","q":"Under the terms of the agreement, either party may ___ the contract with 60 days' written notice.","c":["dismiss","expire","terminate","abolish"],"a":2,"exp":"terminate a contract「契約を解除する」が定型。(B)abolish は制度・法律の廃止。(C)expire は自動詞「期限が切れる」。(D)dismiss は解雇する・却下する。"},
{"id":115,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"The keynote address has been rescheduled ___ a conflict with the opening ceremony.","c":["because","so that","due to","now that"],"a":2,"exp":"後ろが名詞句 a conflict なので前置詞 due to「〜が原因で」が正解。(B)because は接続詞でSVが必要。(C)(D)も接続詞。"},
{"id":116,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"Starting next month, all overtime requests ___ by a department supervisor in advance.","c":["must be approved","must have approved","must approve","must approving"],"a":0,"exp":"requests は「承認される」側なので受動態 must be approved が正解。助動詞+受動態の形。能動・受動の判断問題。"},
{"id":117,"cat":"語彙","q":"The quality assurance team conducts ___ inspections of the production line every quarter.","c":["vigorous","rigorous","strenuous","tremendous"],"a":1,"exp":"rigorous inspection「厳格な検査」が定型コロケーション。(B)strenuous は「骨の折れる(運動など)」、(C)vigorous は「精力的な」、(D)tremendous は「途方もない」。-ous 形容詞の識別。"},
{"id":118,"cat":"品詞","q":"___ for the position must have at least five years of experience in supply chain management.","c":["Applicants","Apply","Applied","Applications"],"a":0,"exp":"must have の主語になる「人」の名詞 Applicants「応募者」が正解。(C)Applications「応募書類」は経験を持てないので不可。人 vs 物の名詞の識別問題。"},
{"id":119,"cat":"その他","q":"The two research teams worked independently, yet ___ reached remarkably similar conclusions.","c":["one another","either","both","each other"],"a":2,"exp":"動詞 reached の主語になれる both「両者とも」が正解。(C)(D)は「お互い」で目的語にしかなれない。(B)either は yet 以下の文意(2チームとも到達)に合わない。"},
{"id":120,"cat":"語彙","q":"Ms. Navarro was promoted to senior editor in ___ of her outstanding contributions to the magazine.","c":["perception","gratitude","recognition","admission"],"a":2,"exp":"in recognition of ~「〜を評価して、〜が認められて」が定型表現。昇進・受賞の文脈で極めて頻出。"},
{"id":121,"cat":"品詞","q":"The billing error was corrected ___ after the customer brought it to the manager's attention.","c":["prompted","promptly","promptness","prompt"],"a":1,"exp":"was corrected という受動態を修飾する副詞 promptly「速やかに」が正解。"},
{"id":122,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"___ the CEO nor the CFO was available to comment on the acquisition rumors.","c":["Both","Neither","Either","Not only"],"a":1,"exp":"nor とペアになるのは Neither。neither A nor B「AもBも〜ない」。(A)Either は or、(D)Not only は but also とペア。相関接続詞の組み合わせ問題。"},
{"id":123,"cat":"語彙","q":"The manufacturer offers a lifetime warranty, which ___ it apart from its competitors.","c":["sets","takes","makes","puts"],"a":0,"exp":"set A apart from B「AをBと差別化する」が定型句動詞。競合との差別化の文脈で頻出。"},
{"id":124,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"Not until the final quarter ___ signs of recovery in the domestic market.","c":["did the analysts see","the analysts saw","the analysts did see","saw the analysts"],"a":0,"exp":"否定語句 Not until ~ が文頭に出ると主節は倒置(疑問文の語順)になる。did the analysts see が正解。倒置の頻出パターン。"},
{"id":125,"cat":"品詞","q":"The architect's design cleverly maximizes natural light while ensuring the ___ of residents.","c":["privatize","privately","privacy","private"],"a":2,"exp":"冠詞 the の後ろ+of の前なので名詞 privacy が正解。ensure the privacy of ~「〜のプライバシーを確保する」。"},
{"id":126,"cat":"語彙","q":"Participation in the stock purchase plan is entirely ___, and employees may opt out at any time.","c":["tentative","arbitrary","spontaneous","voluntary"],"a":3,"exp":"voluntary「任意の、自発的な」が正解。opt out「不参加を選ぶ」できることから任意と分かる。(B)spontaneous 自然発生的な、(D)arbitrary 恣意的な。"},
{"id":127,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"The intern completed the data entry assignment ___ supervision, impressing the entire department.","c":["unless","out","except","without"],"a":3,"exp":"without supervision「監督なしで」。前置詞 without+名詞。(B)unless は接続詞。(C)except は「〜を除いて」で文意に合わない。"},
{"id":128,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The museum curator ___ the 18th-century paintings when she discovered an unknown artist's signature.","c":["was cataloging","cataloged","catalogs","has cataloged"],"a":0,"exp":"when 以下の過去の一時点に進行中だった動作なので過去進行形 was cataloging が正解。「目録作成中に発見した」。"},
{"id":129,"cat":"語彙","q":"Please complete the enclosed survey and return it ___ your earliest convenience.","c":["at","in","with","on"],"a":0,"exp":"at your earliest convenience「ご都合がつき次第」が定型表現。ビジネスレターの決まり文句として頻出。"},
{"id":130,"cat":"品詞","q":"Freelance contractors are responsible for the ___ submission of their own tax documents.","c":["timed","time","timing","timely"],"a":3,"exp":"名詞 submission を修飾する形容詞 timely「期限内の」が正解。timely は形容詞である点が問われる頻出単語。timely submission「期限内の提出」。"},
{"id":131,"cat":"語彙","q":"The workshop leader encouraged participants to think ___ when approaching complex problems.","c":["urgently","abruptly","densely","critically"],"a":3,"exp":"think critically「批判的に考える」が定型コロケーション。(B)urgently 緊急に、(C)abruptly 突然に、(D)densely 密集して。"},
{"id":132,"cat":"その他","q":"The vice president, along with three department heads, ___ visiting the Singapore office next week.","c":["were","have been","are","is"],"a":3,"exp":"主語は単数の The vice president。along with 以下は挿入句で数に影響しない。よって is が正解。id:24と同じく主述一致のひっかけパターン。"},
{"id":133,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"___ heavy rain is forecast for the weekend, the outdoor market will proceed as planned under large tents.","c":["Although","However","Otherwise","Despite"],"a":0,"exp":"後ろにSV(rain is forecast)が続き「雨予報にもかかわらず開催」という譲歩なので接続詞 Although が正解。(B)Despite は前置詞、(C)(D)は副詞。"},
{"id":134,"cat":"語彙","q":"The new booking system allows travelers to ___ their reservations up to 24 hours before departure.","c":["adapt","modify","convert","transform"],"a":1,"exp":"modify a reservation「予約を変更する」が自然。(B)adapt は環境への適応、(C)convert は別形式への変換、(D)transform は大幅な変身。「一部変更」は modify。"},
{"id":135,"cat":"品詞","q":"The panel discussion offered ___ insights into emerging trends in renewable energy investment.","c":["value","values","valuably","valuable"],"a":3,"exp":"名詞 insights を修飾する形容詞 valuable「貴重な」が正解。valuable insights は頻出コロケーション。"},
{"id":136,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"Once approved, the funds ___ to the research team's account within five business days.","c":["are transferring","transfer","have transferred","will be transferred"],"a":3,"exp":"funds は「送金される」側なので受動態。主節なので未来形 will be transferred が正解。Once approved は Once they are approved の短縮。"},
{"id":137,"cat":"語彙","q":"Attendees praised the conference organizers for the ___ planned schedule of events.","c":["spaciously","meticulously","previously","voluntarily"],"a":1,"exp":"meticulously planned「綿密に計画された」が定型。過去分詞 planned を修飾する副詞の語彙問題。(D)previously planned も文法上可能だが「賞賛した」理由としては meticulously が適切。"},
{"id":138,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"All returns must be accompanied ___ the original receipt and packaging.","c":["with","by","to","from"],"a":1,"exp":"be accompanied by ~「〜が添えられている」。accompany の受動態は by を取るのが原則。付帯の by は盲点になりやすい。"},
{"id":139,"cat":"品詞","q":"Store managers have the ___ to offer discounts of up to 15 percent without regional approval.","c":["authorize","authority","authoritatively","authoritative"],"a":1,"exp":"the の後ろ+to 不定詞の前で have の目的語となる名詞 authority「権限」が正解。have the authority to do「〜する権限がある」。"},
{"id":140,"cat":"語彙","q":"The pharmaceutical company's stock price rose ___ following the announcement of the successful clinical trial.","c":["intensely","severely","acutely","sharply"],"a":3,"exp":"rise sharply「急騰する」が定型コロケーション。(B)acutely は鋭敏に(感覚)、(C)severely は深刻に(被害)、(D)intensely は強烈に(感情)。"},
{"id":141,"cat":"その他","q":"The consultant recommended restructuring the department rather than ___ additional staff.","c":["to hire","hire","hiring","hired"],"a":2,"exp":"rather than の前後は同じ形で並列する。restructuring(動名詞)と並ぶのは hiring。A rather than B の並列構造の問題。"},
{"id":142,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"___ its founding in 1985, Meridian Textiles has grown from a small workshop into a global enterprise.","c":["Since","From","When","After that"],"a":0,"exp":"Since its founding「創業以来」+主節が現在完了 has grown。since+名詞で「〜以来」を表し現在完了と呼応する。(B)From だと has grown との呼応が弱い。"},
{"id":143,"cat":"語彙","q":"Managers should provide ___ feedback that helps employees improve rather than discourages them.","c":["instructive","destructive","constructive","productive"],"a":2,"exp":"constructive feedback「建設的なフィードバック」が定型。improve につながる助言という文意。(B)instructive 教育的な、(D)destructive 破壊的な(逆の意味)。"},
{"id":144,"cat":"品詞","q":"The software's user interface was praised for being both intuitive and ___ designed.","c":["elegant","elegancy","elegantly","elegance"],"a":2,"exp":"過去分詞 designed を修飾する副詞 elegantly が正解。both A and B の並列で intuitive(形容詞)と elegantly designed(副詞+分詞)が並ぶ。分詞の前は副詞。"},
{"id":145,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The finance committee postponed ___ a decision until the external audit is complete.","c":["to make","making","make","made"],"a":1,"exp":"postpone は動名詞を目的語に取る動詞。postpone making a decision「決定を先送りする」。to 不定詞は不可。megafeps 系の頻出問題。"},
{"id":146,"cat":"語彙","q":"Julia's Bistro uses only locally ___ ingredients in all of its seasonal dishes.","c":["derived","stemmed","originated","sourced"],"a":3,"exp":"locally sourced ingredients「地元産の食材」が定型表現。source は動詞で「調達する」。(B)(C)(D)は自動詞的用法が中心で ingredients を修飾する過去分詞として不自然。"},
{"id":147,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"Mr. Larsen agreed to chair the committee ___ the condition that meetings be held virtually.","c":["on","in","under","at"],"a":0,"exp":"on the condition that ~「〜という条件で」が定型表現。that 節内の be held は仮定法現在。前置詞のイディオム問題。"},
{"id":148,"cat":"品詞","q":"Demand for the artisanal chocolates has grown ___ since the brand was featured in a popular food magazine.","c":["steadiness","steadier","steady","steadily"],"a":3,"exp":"has grown という動詞を修飾する副詞 steadily「着実に」が正解。grow steadily は頻出コロケーション。"},
{"id":149,"cat":"語彙","q":"The hiring committee will give ___ consideration to candidates with international experience.","c":["desirable","agreeable","favorable","admirable"],"a":2,"exp":"favorable consideration「好意的な検討」が定型。give favorable consideration to ~「〜を優遇して検討する」。(B)agreeable は「感じの良い・同意できる」。"},
{"id":150,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"Visitors are reminded ___ their badges visible at all times while in the facility.","c":["keep","keeping","to keep","kept"],"a":2,"exp":"remind A to do の受動態 be reminded to do「〜するよう注意喚起される」。to keep が正解。remind/encourage/advise+to 不定詞のパターン。"},
{"id":151,"cat":"品詞","q":"The negotiations between the two firms were conducted in the strictest ___ to prevent market speculation.","c":["confident","confidential","confide","confidence"],"a":3,"exp":"in the strictest confidence「極秘に」が定型表現。形容詞 strictest の後ろなので名詞 confidence が正解。(D)confidential は形容詞。"},
{"id":152,"cat":"語彙","q":"The updated employee handbook ___ the previous version issued in 2023.","c":["overtakes","surpasses","supersedes","outweighs"],"a":2,"exp":"supersede「(新版が旧版に)取って代わる」が正解。文書・規則の更新の文脈で頻出。(B)overtake 追い抜く、(C)surpass 上回る(数値・質)、(D)outweigh 〜より重要である。"},
{"id":153,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"___ you have any questions about your benefits enrollment, please contact the HR help desk.","c":["Should","Might","Could","Would"],"a":0,"exp":"Should you have ~ = If you should have ~ の倒置。「万一〜があれば」を表す仮定法の倒置で、文頭に置けるのは Should。ビジネス文書で極めて頻出。"},
{"id":154,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The catering order needs ___ by Thursday if we want delivery before the weekend event.","c":["confirmed","to confirm","confirming","to be confirmed"],"a":3,"exp":"order は「確認される」側なので受動の to be confirmed が正解。need to be done = need doing。(B)confirming も文法上可(need doing)だが選択肢では to be confirmed が標準的。"},
{"id":155,"cat":"品詞","q":"The travel expenses were ___ documented, so the reimbursement was processed without delay.","c":["properly","proper","properness","propriety"],"a":0,"exp":"were documented という受動態の間に入る副詞 properly「適切に」が正解。be動詞+副詞+過去分詞の頻出パターン。"},
{"id":156,"cat":"語彙","q":"To ___ with international safety standards, the factory upgraded its fire suppression system.","c":["conform","abide","adhere","comply"],"a":3,"exp":"comply with ~「〜を遵守する」。(B)adhere to、(C)conform to、(D)abide by と、それぞれ取る前置詞が異なる。with を取るのは comply。前置詞との組み合わせ問題。"},
{"id":157,"cat":"品詞","q":"Ms. Duval handled the difficult client negotiation with remarkable ___.","c":["professionalism","professional","profession","professionally"],"a":0,"exp":"前置詞 with+形容詞 remarkable の後ろなので名詞 professionalism「プロ意識」が正解。(D)profession は「職業」で文意に合わない。名詞の意味の識別まで問う問題。"},
{"id":158,"cat":"その他","q":"The company offers two retirement plans, ___ of which include employer matching contributions.","c":["every","all","either","both"],"a":3,"exp":"two plans を受けて「その両方が」となる both of which が正解。(C)every は of を取れない。(D)all は3つ以上。数量詞+of which の関係詞問題。"},
{"id":159,"cat":"語彙","q":"The marketing campaign was specifically ___ to appeal to environmentally conscious consumers.","c":["stitched","woven","trimmed","tailored"],"a":3,"exp":"be tailored to ~「〜に合わせて作られる」。tailor は仕立てる→カスタマイズするの比喩で頻出。(B)(C)(D)は縫製関連の literal な動詞で比喩用法がない。"},
{"id":160,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"The new regulations will take effect ___ January 1, giving companies six months to prepare.","c":["as to","as for","as of","as in"],"a":2,"exp":"as of+日付「〜付けで、〜をもって」が定型表現。効力発生日を表す頻出表現。(B)as to 〜に関して、(C)as for 〜はどうかと言えば。"},
{"id":161,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"Ms. Tanaka would rather the quarterly review meeting ___ to next week.","c":["is moved","were moved","be moved","will be moved"],"a":1,"exp":"would rather+that節では過去形(仮定法過去)を使うのが標準。were moved が正解。would rather S+過去形「Sが〜すればいいのにと思う」。上級文法問題。"},
{"id":162,"cat":"語彙","q":"The auditor found a minor ___ between the reported figures and the actual inventory count.","c":["discrepancy","deviation","interference","controversy"],"a":0,"exp":"discrepancy between A and B「AとBの間の食い違い」が定型。会計・監査の文脈で頻出。(D)deviation は「基準からの逸脱」で from を取る。"},
{"id":163,"cat":"品詞","q":"___ speaking, the merger will not affect day-to-day operations at either company.","c":["Practical","Practiced","Practice","Practically"],"a":3,"exp":"practically speaking「実際的に言えば」。〜ly speaking(generally/strictly/frankly speaking)は文修飾の定型で副詞が入る。"},
{"id":164,"cat":"語彙","q":"Employees who travel abroad for business are ___ to a daily meal allowance of $75.","c":["entitled","granted","deserved","awarded"],"a":0,"exp":"be entitled to ~「〜を受ける権利がある」が定型。(C)granted と(D)awarded は be granted/awarded+名詞(to なし)の形を取る。前置詞 to が決め手。"},
{"id":165,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"The seminar room can accommodate up to fifty participants, ___ makes it ideal for department-wide training.","c":["which","that","it","what"],"a":0,"exp":"前の節全体を先行詞とする非制限用法の関係代名詞 which が正解。カンマの後ろで that は使えない。(D)it だと接続詞がなく2文がつながらない。"},
{"id":166,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"Had it not been for the backup generator, the data center ___ a complete shutdown during the storm.","c":["would have experienced","would experience","experienced","will experience"],"a":0,"exp":"Had it not been for ~「〜がなかったら」(仮定法過去完了の倒置)。帰結節は would have+過去分詞。過去の事実に反する仮定の上級パターン。"},
{"id":167,"cat":"語彙","q":"The customer survey revealed an ___ preference for the matte finish over the glossy option.","c":["overbearing","overacting","overlooking","overwhelming"],"a":3,"exp":"overwhelming preference「圧倒的な支持」が定型コロケーション。(B)overbearing は「横柄な」、over- で始まる紛らわしい語の識別問題。"},
{"id":168,"cat":"品詞","q":"All safety incidents, ___ minor, must be reported to the site supervisor immediately.","c":["however","how","whatever","whichever"],"a":0,"exp":"however+形容詞「どんなに〜でも」の譲歩用法。however minor (they are)「どんなに軽微でも」。(C)whatever は名詞を伴う。"},
{"id":169,"cat":"語彙","q":"The board decided to ___ the dividend payment in light of the company's strong cash position.","c":["rise","arouse","raise","arise"],"a":2,"exp":"raise「〜を引き上げる」(他動詞)が正解。目的語 the dividend payment があるので他動詞が必要。(B)rise と(C)arise は自動詞。raise/rise の識別は定番。"},
{"id":170,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"___ the projector nor the microphone was working when the presenters arrived at the venue.","c":["Not","Either","Neither","Both"],"a":2,"exp":"nor とペアになる Neither が正解。Neither A nor B が主語のとき動詞は原則B(単数)に一致し was となっている点も整合。"},
{"id":171,"cat":"品詞","q":"The device automatically switches to power-saving mode when it detects ___ activity.","c":["prolonged","prolong","prolonging","prolongation"],"a":0,"exp":"名詞 activity を修飾する過去分詞由来の形容詞... 実は文意は「不活動が続いたとき」なので prolonged inactivity が自然だが、ここでは prolonged「長時間の」が activity を修飾する形容詞として正解。(C)prolonging は「延長させつつある」で不自然。"},
{"id":172,"cat":"語彙","q":"Shuttle buses to the convention center depart from the hotel lobby ___ hour on the half hour.","c":["all","each other","most","every"],"a":3,"exp":"every hour「毎時」。on the half hour「毎時30分に」と合わせて「毎時30分発」。単数名詞 hour に付くのは every。(C)all/(D)most は複数形が必要。"},
{"id":173,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"The product recall was handled so efficiently ___ customer trust in the brand actually increased.","c":["that","as","which","than"],"a":0,"exp":"so ~ that ...「非常に〜なので…」の構文。so efficiently that が正解。so と that の間が離れていても見抜けるかを問う問題。"},
{"id":174,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The legal department advised ___ the licensing agreement before the trade show.","c":["renew","to renew","renewing","renewal to"],"a":2,"exp":"advise は目的語なしで直接動名詞を取る(advise doing)。advise A to do の形なら to 不定詞だが、ここは目的語(人)がないので renewing が正解。"},
{"id":175,"cat":"語彙","q":"The two branch offices will be ___ into a single regional headquarters by next summer.","c":["compressed","condensed","consolidated","constrained"],"a":2,"exp":"consolidate「(組織・事業所を)統合する」が正解。オフィス統合の文脈で頻出。(B)condense は液体・文章の凝縮、(C)compress は物理的圧縮。"},
{"id":176,"cat":"品詞","q":"Ms. Reyes is ___ regarded by colleagues for her ability to mediate difficult negotiations.","c":["high","highly","height","higher"],"a":1,"exp":"be highly regarded「高く評価されている」が定型。highly は「非常に」という程度の副詞。high は「(物理的に)高く」でここでは不可。high/highly の識別問題。"},
{"id":177,"cat":"その他","q":"Sales figures for this quarter are significantly better than ___ of the same period last year.","c":["that","them","those","ones"],"a":2,"exp":"複数名詞 sales figures の繰り返しを避ける代名詞 those が正解。比較構文での that/those の使い分け(単数=that、複数=those)は頻出。"},
{"id":178,"cat":"語彙","q":"Please note that the express delivery option ___ an additional fee of $15.","c":["incurs","costs","spends","charges"],"a":0,"exp":"incur a fee「料金が発生する」。主語が option(サービス)で目的語が fee の組み合わせでは incur が最も自然。(C)charges は主語が業者、(D)costs は cost+人+金額の形。"},
{"id":179,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"___ what many analysts predicted, the housing market remained stable throughout the year.","c":["Contrary to","Opposed","In contrast","Unlike that"],"a":0,"exp":"contrary to ~「〜に反して」。contrary to what SV「〜が…したことに反して」の形で頻出。(C)In contrast は単独では目的語を取れず in contrast to の形が必要。"},
{"id":180,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The IT team spent the entire weekend ___ the security vulnerabilities identified in the audit.","c":["patching","to patch","patched","patch"],"a":0,"exp":"spend+時間+doing「〜するのに時間を費やす」。patching が正解。spend の後ろの動名詞は頻出パターン。"},
{"id":181,"cat":"語彙","q":"The new CFO implemented several measures to ___ costs without compromising product quality.","c":["curb","crave","curve","carve"],"a":0,"exp":"curb costs「コストを抑制する」。curb は「抑制する」の意味で頻出。(B)curve 曲線、(C)carve 彫る、(D)crave 切望する。スペルが似た語のひっかけ。"},
{"id":182,"cat":"品詞","q":"The panel members offered ___ opinions on whether the city should invest in light rail.","c":["different","differ","difference","differently"],"a":0,"exp":"名詞 opinions を修飾する形容詞 different が正解。動詞 differ、副詞 differently、名詞 difference との識別。基本だが取りこぼせない品詞問題。"},
{"id":183,"cat":"語彙","q":"Registration fees are fully refundable up to two weeks before the event; ___, a 50 percent cancellation charge applies.","c":["likewise","thereafter","moreover","meanwhile"],"a":1,"exp":"thereafter「それ以降は」が正解。「2週間前までは全額返金、それ以降は50%」という時間的対比。(B)meanwhile その間、(C)moreover さらに、(D)likewise 同様に。"},
{"id":184,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"Digital receipts are now standard, ___ customers may request printed copies at checkout.","c":["despite","whereas that","although","unless"],"a":2,"exp":"「デジタルが標準だが、印刷版も要求できる」という譲歩・対比を表す接続詞 although が正解。(D)whereas that という形は存在しない。"},
{"id":185,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"Since joining the firm, Mr. Adeyemi ___ three major infrastructure projects across West Africa.","c":["oversaw","oversees","has overseen","overseeing"],"a":2,"exp":"Since joining ~「入社以来」があるので現在完了 has overseen が正解。since は現在完了のシグナル。(A)oversaw(過去形)は since と共起しない。"},
{"id":186,"cat":"語彙","q":"The company's travel policy ___ that employees book economy class for flights under six hours.","c":["insists","compels","mandates","enforces"],"a":2,"exp":"mandate that ~「〜と義務づける」。policy を主語に that 節を取れるのは mandate。(B)insist は insist that も可だが「主張する」で規則の文脈では mandate が適切。(C)enforce/(D)compel は that 節を取らない。"},
{"id":187,"cat":"品詞","q":"Analysts remain ___ about the retail sector's prospects despite recent gains in consumer spending.","c":["caution","cautiously","cautioned","cautious"],"a":3,"exp":"remain+形容詞「〜のままである」。cautious「慎重な」が正解。remain の補語は形容詞という頻出パターン。"},
{"id":188,"cat":"その他","q":"Very few of the original founding members are still with the company, and ___ remain hold senior advisory roles.","c":["which","they who","whoever","those who"],"a":3,"exp":"those who remain「残っている人々」。動詞 remain と hold の2つがあるため関係詞節を作る those who が必要。(D)they who は現代英語では不自然。"},
{"id":189,"cat":"語彙","q":"The prototype performed well in ___ tests, but further trials are needed before mass production.","c":["predominant","precautionary","preposterous","preliminary"],"a":3,"exp":"preliminary tests「予備試験」が定型。「さらなる試験が必要」から初期段階の試験と分かる。(B)precautionary 予防的な、(D)predominant 支配的な。pre- で始まる語の識別。"},
{"id":190,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"Coupons cannot be combined with any other offer, ___ otherwise stated on the coupon itself.","c":["unless","if","without","except"],"a":0,"exp":"unless otherwise stated「別段の記載がない限り」が定型表現。契約書・クーポンの但し書きで極めて頻出。丸ごと覚えるべきフレーズ。"},
{"id":191,"cat":"品詞","q":"The orientation session gave new hires a ___ understanding of the company's core values.","c":["deepen","deeply","deep","depth"],"a":2,"exp":"名詞 understanding を修飾する形容詞 deep が正解。a deep understanding of ~「〜への深い理解」。(B)deepen は動詞「深める」。"},
{"id":192,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The contract stipulates that any disputes ___ through arbitration rather than litigation.","c":["are resolved","be resolved","will resolve","resolved"],"a":1,"exp":"stipulate that 節内は仮定法現在(動詞の原形)。受動なので be resolved。stipulate/mandate/require の that 節は原形という上級頻出パターン。"},
{"id":193,"cat":"語彙","q":"Ticket sales for the charity gala have been ___ brisk, with only a few seats remaining.","c":["remarkably","precisely","approximately","virtually"],"a":0,"exp":"remarkably brisk「著しく好調」。brisk(売れ行きが良い)を強調する副詞は remarkably。(C)virtually は「事実上」で形容詞の程度を強めない。"},
{"id":194,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"___ the scope of the renovation, the museum will remain closed for at least eight months.","c":["Providing","Given","Considered","Assuming"],"a":1,"exp":"Given+名詞「〜を考慮すると」。前置詞的に使える Given が正解。(B)Providing/(C)Assuming は接続詞的でSVが続く。(D)Considered は Considering なら可。"},
{"id":195,"cat":"語彙","q":"The airline ___ passengers for the delay with meal vouchers and hotel accommodations.","c":["refunded","compensated","rewarded","reimbursed"],"a":1,"exp":"compensate A for B「AにBの埋め合わせをする」。(B)refund は代金の払い戻し、(C)reimburse は立替金の精算で、食事券・宿泊の提供は compensate が適切。"},
{"id":196,"cat":"品詞","q":"Employees are evaluated ___ on the basis of measurable performance indicators.","c":["objectively","objectivity","object","objective"],"a":0,"exp":"are evaluated という受動態を修飾する副詞 objectively「客観的に」が正解。"},
{"id":197,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"No sooner ___ the store opened its doors than customers rushed toward the clearance section.","c":["was","did","had","has"],"a":2,"exp":"No sooner had S+過去分詞 ~ than ...「〜するやいなや…」。No sooner が文頭に出ると過去完了の倒置になる。No sooner had the store opened が正解。上級倒置構文。"},
{"id":198,"cat":"語彙","q":"The committee will ___ the feasibility of relocating the distribution center to a site near the port.","c":["assert","assort","assess","access"],"a":2,"exp":"assess the feasibility「実現可能性を評価する」。(B)access はスペルが似た「アクセスする」、(D)assert は「主張する」。assess/access の識別は定番のひっかけ。"},
{"id":199,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"The memo was distributed to all staff ___ that everyone would be informed of the policy change before Monday.","c":["such","in order","for","so"],"a":3,"exp":"so that S+would「〜するように」の目的構文。so that が正解。(B)in order は in order that なら可だが in order 単独では不可。"},
{"id":200,"cat":"語彙","q":"Despite the ambitious timeline, the construction crew completed the bridge repairs ___ schedule.","c":["ahead of","prior","in front of","before of"],"a":0,"exp":"ahead of schedule「予定より早く」が定型表現。behind schedule(遅れて)、on schedule(予定通り)とセットで頻出。(D)before of という形は存在しない。"},
{"id":201,"cat":"品詞","q":"The factory's output has increased ___ since the installation of the automated assembly line.","c":["dramatics","dramatically","dramatize","dramatic"],"a":1,"exp":"has increased という動詞を修飾する副詞 dramatically「劇的に」が正解。increase dramatically は頻出コロケーション。"},
{"id":202,"cat":"語彙","q":"All laboratory personnel must wear protective gear when handling ___ materials.","c":["hazardous","jeopardized","endangered","hazard"],"a":0,"exp":"hazardous materials「危険物」が定型表現。(B)hazard は名詞。(D)endangered は「絶滅の危機にある(種)」で materials には使わない。"},
{"id":203,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"The invoice must be paid in full ___ thirty days of the delivery date to avoid late fees.","c":["within","during","since","until"],"a":0,"exp":"within ~ days of ...「…から〜日以内に」。期限を表す within。(B)until は継続の終点で「支払う」という一回の動作には不適。"},
{"id":204,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"___ the annual budget review, department heads are asked to prepare detailed expenditure reports.","c":["In preparation for","Prepared","Being prepared","To preparing"],"a":0,"exp":"in preparation for ~「〜に備えて」が定型表現。(B)To preparing という形は不可(to 不定詞なら to prepare)。"},
{"id":205,"cat":"品詞","q":"Critics described the architect's latest design as both functional and ___ striking.","c":["visual","visually","visualize","vision"],"a":1,"exp":"形容詞 striking を修飾する副詞 visually「視覚的に」が正解。visually striking「見た目に印象的な」。形容詞の前の空所は副詞。"},
{"id":206,"cat":"語彙","q":"The company has taken significant steps to reduce its carbon ___ over the past decade.","c":["fingerprint","imprint","blueprint","footprint"],"a":3,"exp":"carbon footprint「二酸化炭素排出量、カーボンフットプリント」が定型表現。環境関連の頻出語。(D)blueprint は「設計図、青写真」。"},
{"id":207,"cat":"品詞","q":"___ of the new inventory system will begin next month, starting with the Osaka warehouse.","c":["Implementation","Implementing","Implemented","Implement"],"a":0,"exp":"文頭で主語となり of を伴う名詞 Implementation「導入」が正解。動詞 will begin の主語が必要。(D)Implementing(動名詞)は「導入すること が始まる」でやや不自然、名詞が優先。"},
{"id":208,"cat":"その他","q":"Ms. Fontaine asked her assistant to book a flight for ___ and the two visiting executives.","c":["herself","her","she","hers"],"a":1,"exp":"前置詞 for の目的語で、主語(assistant)と異なる人物を指すので目的格 her が正解。herself は主語と同一人物のときのみ。再帰代名詞のひっかけ問題。"},
{"id":209,"cat":"語彙","q":"Please ___ the enclosed form and return it in the prepaid envelope by June 15.","c":["fill over","fill away","fill out","fill up"],"a":2,"exp":"fill out a form「用紙に記入する」が定型句動詞。(B)fill up は「満タンにする」。"},
{"id":210,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"The restaurant accepts reservations ___ up to eight people; larger groups should call directly.","c":["with","for","among","of"],"a":1,"exp":"reservations for ~ people「〜名の予約」。人数を表す for。前置詞の基本用法だが意外と迷いやすい。"},
{"id":211,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The proposal ___ by the review board at the time the funding announcement was made.","c":["still evaluated","was still being evaluated","has still evaluated","is still evaluated"],"a":1,"exp":"at the time ~「〜の時点で」という過去の時点で進行中+受動なので過去進行形の受動態 was still being evaluated が正解。being を含む受動進行形は上級パターン。"},
{"id":212,"cat":"語彙","q":"Sales of the flagship model remained ___ even as competitors slashed their prices.","c":["muscular","robust","intense","forceful"],"a":1,"exp":"robust sales「堅調な売上」が定型コロケーション。robust は「(数値・経済が)堅調な」で頻出。(B)muscular は文字通り筋肉の。"},
{"id":213,"cat":"品詞","q":"The seminar provided ___ advice on how to negotiate vendor contracts effectively.","c":["practically","practical","practice","practicing"],"a":1,"exp":"名詞 advice を修飾する形容詞 practical「実用的な」が正解。practical advice は頻出コロケーション。"},
{"id":214,"cat":"語彙","q":"Because the flight was overbooked, the airline offered travel vouchers to passengers willing to take a ___ flight.","c":["late","lately","later","latter"],"a":2,"exp":"later flight「後の便」。比較の意味を含む later が正解。(B)late は「遅れた」、(C)lately は副詞「最近」、(D)latter は「(2つのうち)後者の」。late 系の識別問題。"},
{"id":215,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"___ the poor weather forecast, organizers decided to move the award ceremony indoors.","c":["In place of","In light of","With regard","On account"],"a":1,"exp":"in light of ~「〜を踏まえて」が正解。(C)On account は on account of、(D)With regard は with regard to の形が必要。前置詞句の完全形を問う問題。"},
{"id":216,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"Neither the design team nor the project manager ___ aware of the change in specifications.","c":["was","are","have been","were"],"a":0,"exp":"neither A nor B が主語のとき、動詞は近い方のB(the project manager=単数)に一致する。よって was が正解。近接の原則を問う上級の主述一致。"},
{"id":217,"cat":"語彙","q":"The bank offers a ___ range of investment products to suit clients at every stage of life.","c":["divided","doubtful","distant","diverse"],"a":3,"exp":"a diverse range of ~「多様な〜」が定型。a wide/broad/diverse range of は頻出パターン。"},
{"id":218,"cat":"品詞","q":"The CEO's speech was surprisingly ___, lasting less than ten minutes.","c":["conciseness","concision","concisely","concise"],"a":3,"exp":"was の補語となる形容詞 concise「簡潔な」が正解。be動詞+副詞 surprisingly+空所の形では形容詞が入る。"},
{"id":219,"cat":"その他","q":"Of all the applicants interviewed this month, Ms. Khoury demonstrated ___ understanding of regional market dynamics.","c":["more deeply","deep","deeper","the deepest"],"a":3,"exp":"Of all ~「すべての中で」があるので最上級 the deepest が正解。範囲を示す語句から最上級を選ぶパターン。"},
{"id":220,"cat":"語彙","q":"Construction noise will be kept to a ___ during the hotel's business hours.","c":["minimum","minor","minimal","minimize"],"a":0,"exp":"keep ~ to a minimum「〜を最小限に抑える」が定型表現。冠詞 a の後ろなので名詞 minimum。(B)minimal は形容詞。品詞と語彙の複合問題。"},
{"id":221,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"Mr. Boateng will serve as interim director ___ a permanent replacement is appointed.","c":["while","until","by","during"],"a":1,"exp":"「後任が任命されるまで(継続して)」なので until が正解。serve という継続動作+終点は until。by は期限までの完了。until/by の識別問題。"},
{"id":222,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The research grant application, if ___ by the committee, will fund the project for three years.","c":["to approve","approving","approved","approves"],"a":2,"exp":"if approved = if it is approved の省略形。application は「承認される」側なので過去分詞 approved が正解。if+過去分詞の省略構文。"},
{"id":223,"cat":"語彙","q":"The hotel's concierge staff is renowned for ___ to guests' requests promptly and courteously.","c":["serving","catering","attending","responding"],"a":2,"exp":"attend to ~「〜に対応する」。requests との組み合わせで前置詞 to を取るのは attend と respond だが、(D)responding でも文意は通る...ただし attend to requests がホテル文脈の定型。※respond to も可のため、実際の試験では attend が「世話をする」ニュアンスで優先。"},
{"id":224,"cat":"品詞","q":"Digital subscriptions now account for ___ two-thirds of the newspaper's total revenue.","c":["approximation","approximated","approximately","approximate"],"a":2,"exp":"数値表現 two-thirds を修飾する副詞 approximately「約」が正解。数字の前の空所は approximately/nearly/roughly などの副詞。"},
{"id":225,"cat":"語彙","q":"New regulations require that food labels ___ list all potential allergens.","c":["implicitly","scarcely","abruptly","explicitly"],"a":3,"exp":"explicitly list「明示的に記載する」。ラベル表示の文脈では「はっきりと」の explicitly。(B)implicitly「暗黙的に」は正反対の意味。"},
{"id":226,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"___ arriving at the hotel, guests are invited to enjoy a complimentary welcome drink in the lounge.","c":["Upon","During","At","While"],"a":0,"exp":"upon -ing「〜するとすぐに」。upon arriving = as soon as they arrive。(C)While も -ing を取れるが「到着している間」となり不自然。"},
{"id":227,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The board meeting ___ for three hours when the chairman finally called for a vote.","c":["was going on","has gone on","had been going on","went on"],"a":2,"exp":"「議長が採決を求めた(過去)時点まで3時間続いていた」ので過去完了進行形 had been going on が正解。for three hours+過去の基準点=過去完了進行形。"},
{"id":228,"cat":"語彙","q":"To streamline operations, the company will ___ several routine administrative tasks to an outside firm.","c":["undertake","outsource","downsize","overhaul"],"a":1,"exp":"outsource A to B「AをBに外部委託する」。to an outside firm が決め手。(B)overhaul 全面改修する、(C)undertake 引き受ける(逆方向)、(D)downsize 縮小する。"},
{"id":229,"cat":"品詞","q":"Ms. Silva's promotion to regional director was a ___ deserved recognition of her decade of service.","c":["rich","riches","richly","richness"],"a":2,"exp":"過去分詞由来の形容詞 deserved を修飾する副詞 richly が正解。richly deserved「十分に値する」は定型コロケーション。"},
{"id":230,"cat":"その他","q":"Each department must submit ___ own budget projections by the end of the fiscal year.","c":["it","their","its","theirs"],"a":2,"exp":"each department は単数扱いなので所有格は its が正解。「each+単数名詞→its」の一致は頻出ひっかけ。their を選ばせようとする典型問題。"},
{"id":231,"cat":"語彙","q":"The keynote presentation will address emerging trends, ___ by a panel discussion with industry experts.","c":["to follow","followed","follows","following"],"a":1,"exp":"followed by ~「その後に〜が続く」が定型。プレゼンの後にパネル討論が「続く」ので受動の followed。(B)following だと「〜に続いて」で順序が逆になる。"},
{"id":232,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"Employees must obtain written authorization ___ using company vehicles for personal errands.","c":["despite","toward","until","before"],"a":3,"exp":"before -ing「〜する前に」。「私用で社用車を使う前に許可を得る」。(B)until だと「使うまで許可を得続ける」で不自然。"},
{"id":233,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"It is essential that every expense report ___ original receipts for all purchases over $25.","c":["include","includes","included","including"],"a":0,"exp":"It is essential that 節内は動詞の原形(仮定法現在)。every expense report は単数だが include に s は付かない。essential/important/necessary+that 節も原形。"},
{"id":234,"cat":"語彙","q":"After weeks of testing, the engineers finally identified the ___ of the intermittent power failure.","c":["source","outlet","resource","origin place"],"a":0,"exp":"identify the source of ~「〜の原因を特定する」。問題・故障の「発生源」は source。(B)resource は「資源」。"},
{"id":235,"cat":"品詞","q":"The gallery's collection of contemporary sculpture is ___ among regional museums.","c":["distinctly","distinctive","distinction","distinct"],"a":1,"exp":"be動詞の補語となる形容詞。distinctive「独自の、特色のある」が正解。(A)distinct は「別個の、明確な」で from を伴うことが多い。distinct/distinctive の意味の識別まで問う難問。"},
{"id":236,"cat":"語彙","q":"Employees are encouraged to ___ advantage of the tuition reimbursement program.","c":["make","have","get","take"],"a":3,"exp":"take advantage of ~「〜を活用する」が定型イディオム。動詞+advantage の組み合わせは take のみ。"},
{"id":237,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"The software license permits installation on up to three devices, ___ they are registered to the same user.","c":["as long as","in that case","even so","only"],"a":0,"exp":"「同一ユーザー登録という条件で」を表す接続詞 as long as が正解。後ろにSVが続く。(B)(C)は副詞的表現。"},
{"id":238,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"A revised organizational chart ___ to the company intranet by the time you read this memo.","c":["will upload","uploads","will have been uploaded","has uploaded"],"a":2,"exp":"by the time you read this「これを読む時までに」という未来の基準点+chart は「アップロードされる」側なので未来完了の受動態 will have been uploaded が正解。"},
{"id":239,"cat":"語彙","q":"The negotiation stalled because the two sides could not agree on the ___ of the licensing fees.","c":["words","phrases","terms","clauses"],"a":2,"exp":"the terms of ~「〜の条件」。契約・取引の「条件」は terms(複数形)。(D)clauses は契約書の「条項」で、fee の内容そのものには terms が適切。"},
{"id":240,"cat":"品詞","q":"Once ___ , the mobile app allows users to track shipments in real time.","c":["downloads","downloading","downloaded","download"],"a":2,"exp":"Once (it is) downloaded の省略。app は「ダウンロードされる」側なので過去分詞 downloaded が正解。接続詞+過去分詞の省略構文。"},
{"id":241,"cat":"語彙","q":"Ms. Ivanova has a proven ___ record of turning around underperforming retail locations.","c":["running","track","history","past"],"a":1,"exp":"a proven track record「実証済みの実績」が定型表現。track record で「実績」。丸ごと覚えるべきコロケーション。"},
{"id":242,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"Late submissions will not be accepted ___ any circumstances, as stated in the competition rules.","c":["on","at","under","over"],"a":2,"exp":"under no/any circumstances「いかなる状況でも(〜ない)」が定型表現。circumstances と結びつく前置詞は under。"},
{"id":243,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The hiring freeze, ___ last November, will remain in effect until further notice.","c":["was announced","having announced","announcing","announced"],"a":3,"exp":"The hiring freeze (which was) announced last November の省略。freeze は「発表される」側なので過去分詞 announced が正解。挿入句の分詞問題。"},
{"id":244,"cat":"語彙","q":"The city's public transportation system is ___ regarded as one of the most efficient in the region.","c":["broadly openly","spaciously","widely","expansively"],"a":2,"exp":"be widely regarded as ~「〜として広く認められている」が定型。widely+regarded/known/used は頻出の組み合わせ。"},
{"id":245,"cat":"品詞","q":"A ___ percentage of survey respondents indicated a preference for flexible work arrangements.","c":["significance","significantly","signify","significant"],"a":3,"exp":"冠詞 A と名詞 percentage の間なので形容詞 significant「かなりの」が正解。a significant percentage/number of は頻出。"},
{"id":246,"cat":"その他","q":"The company's revenue this year is projected to be nearly double ___ it earned five years ago.","c":["which","that","what","as"],"a":2,"exp":"先行詞を含む関係代名詞 what「〜するもの(=金額)」が正解。double what it earned「稼いだ額の2倍」。(B)that は先行詞が必要。"},
{"id":247,"cat":"語彙","q":"Due to a clerical ___, some customers received duplicate invoices last week.","c":["overlook","oversight","overview","oversee"],"a":1,"exp":"a clerical oversight「事務的な見落とし」。名詞で「見落とし、手落ち」は oversight。(B)overlook は動詞。(D)overview は「概要」。over- 系の名詞・動詞識別。"},
{"id":248,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"___ further notice, the fitness center will close at 8 P.M. instead of 10 P.M.","c":["By","Within","Toward","Until"],"a":3,"exp":"until further notice「追って通知があるまで」が定型表現。営業時間変更などの告知文で極めて頻出。"},
{"id":249,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"Ms. Delacroix requested that the invoice ___ to reflect the agreed-upon discount.","c":["was revised","is revised","revises","be revised"],"a":3,"exp":"request that 節内は動詞の原形(仮定法現在)。受動なので be revised。request/ask/demand の that 節は原形。"},
{"id":250,"cat":"語彙","q":"The two firms announced a strategic ___ to jointly develop battery technology for electric vehicles.","c":["abundance","allowance","appliance","alliance"],"a":3,"exp":"strategic alliance「戦略的提携」が定型表現。(B)appliance 家電、(C)allowance 手当、(D)abundance 豊富さ。-ance で終わる紛らわしい名詞の識別。"},
{"id":251,"cat":"品詞","q":"The finance team identified several ___ in the vendor's billing statements over the past quarter.","c":["inconsistencies","inconsistently","inconsistency","inconsistent"],"a":0,"exp":"several の後ろなので複数形の名詞 inconsistencies「不一致」が正解。several+可算名詞複数形。(D)inconsistency は単数形なので several と合わない。"},
{"id":252,"cat":"語彙","q":"The seminar on cross-cultural communication drew a ___ audience of over three hundred professionals.","c":["capacity","capable","capacious","captive"],"a":0,"exp":"a capacity audience/crowd「満員の聴衆」が定型表現。capacity が名詞のまま形容詞的に使われる。(D)captive audience は「(その場を離れられない)聞かざるを得ない聴衆」で別の意味。"},
{"id":253,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"The product launch was postponed ___ concerns about component shortages could be resolved.","c":["until","despite","unless","by"],"a":0,"exp":"「懸念が解消されるまで延期」なので until が正解。postpone until は自然な組み合わせ。(C)unless では「解消されない限り延期された」となり時制的に不自然。"},
{"id":254,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"___ in 1962, the observatory has welcomed generations of astronomy enthusiasts.","c":["Having founded","Founded","Being found","Founding"],"a":1,"exp":"observatory は「設立された」側なので過去分詞 Founded の分詞構文が正解。(C)Being found は find(見つける)の受動で意味が異なる。found/find の識別も含む問題。"},
{"id":255,"cat":"品詞","q":"The committee found the consultant's analysis remarkably ___ despite the limited data available.","c":["insightful","insights","insightfully","insight"],"a":0,"exp":"find+目的語+補語(形容詞)の第5文型。insightful「洞察に富んだ」が正解。find O C の構文を見抜く問題。"},
{"id":256,"cat":"語彙","q":"Interest in the webinar series has grown steadily, ___ the company to add two additional sessions.","c":["prompting","insisting","urging that","suggesting"],"a":0,"exp":"prompt A to do「Aに〜するよう促す」。分詞構文で prompting the company to add。(B)insist/(C)suggest は目的語+to 不定詞を取れない。"},
{"id":257,"cat":"品詞","q":"Room rates vary ___ depending on the season and day of the week.","c":["considerate","consideration","considerably","considerable"],"a":2,"exp":"動詞 vary を修飾する副詞 considerably「かなり」が正解。vary considerably は頻出。(A)considerate「思いやりのある」と(B)considerable「相当な」の意味の違いにも注意。"},
{"id":258,"cat":"その他","q":"___ the marketing budget nor the timeline has been finalized for the spring campaign.","c":["Either","Whether","Neither","Both"],"a":2,"exp":"nor とペアになる Neither が正解。Neither A nor B+単数動詞 has。相関接続詞と主述一致の複合問題。"},
{"id":259,"cat":"語彙","q":"The auditing firm was hired to conduct an ___ review of the company's financial practices.","c":["impartial","impending","impassive","imperative"],"a":0,"exp":"impartial review「公平な調査」。外部監査の目的は公平性。(B)impassive 無表情な、(C)imperative 必須の、(D)impending 差し迫った。im- で始まる形容詞の識別。"},
{"id":260,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"Payment is due upon receipt of the invoice; ___, a 2 percent discount applies if paid within ten days.","c":["however","furthermore","otherwise","therefore"],"a":0,"exp":"「支払いは受領時が原則。ただし10日以内なら割引」という対比・逆接なので however が正解。セミコロン+接続副詞+カンマの頻出形。"},
{"id":261,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The security system requires all visitors ___ a temporary badge before entering the premises.","c":["to obtain","obtaining","obtain","obtained"],"a":0,"exp":"require A to do「Aに〜するよう求める」。to obtain が正解。require that 節なら原形だが、ここは require+目的語+to 不定詞の形。二つの require 構文の識別。"},
{"id":262,"cat":"語彙","q":"After reviewing the applications, the committee narrowed the list ___ to five finalists.","c":["up","away","down","off"],"a":2,"exp":"narrow down「絞り込む」が定型句動詞。narrow the list down to ~「リストを〜まで絞る」。"},
{"id":263,"cat":"品詞","q":"Ms. Then's ___ handling of the product recall earned her a commendation from the board.","c":["skillfully","skillful","skilled","skill"],"a":1,"exp":"所有格 Ms. Then's と名詞 handling の間なので形容詞 skillful「巧みな」が正解。(B)skilled は「熟練した(人)」で人を修飾することが多く、handling には skillful が自然。"},
{"id":264,"cat":"語彙","q":"The transit authority will ___ additional buses during the international trade fair.","c":["commute","deploy","dispatch permanently","embark"],"a":1,"exp":"deploy「(車両・人員を)配備する、投入する」が正解。増便の文脈。(C)embark は「乗り出す」、(D)commute は「通勤する」。"},
{"id":265,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"___ whether to renew the office lease, management is also considering relocating to the suburbs.","c":["For decide","While to decide","Deciding on","In deciding"],"a":3,"exp":"in deciding ~「〜を決めるにあたって」。in -ing「〜する際に」の用法。(B)Deciding on whether は on が余分。前置詞+動名詞の総合問題。"},
{"id":266,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"Employees ___ to the new office complex will receive relocation assistance of up to $5,000.","c":["transferring","having transferred","transferred","transfer"],"a":2,"exp":"Employees (who are) transferred「転勤させられる従業員」。会社によって転勤「させられる」ので過去分詞 transferred が正解。(B)transferring だと自ら移る意味になり assistance の文脈では transferred が標準。"},
{"id":267,"cat":"語彙","q":"The manual includes a troubleshooting section that addresses the most ___ encountered technical problems.","c":["repetitively","constantly","habitually","frequently"],"a":3,"exp":"frequently encountered「よく遭遇する」が定型。most frequently encountered problems「最もよくある問題」。(B)habitually は人の習慣、(D)constantly は「絶え間なく」。"},
{"id":268,"cat":"品詞","q":"The board expressed ___ over the rising costs of raw materials in the third quarter.","c":["concernedly","concerning","concerned","concern"],"a":3,"exp":"express の目的語となる名詞 concern「懸念」が正解。express concern over/about ~「〜に懸念を表明する」は頻出。"},
{"id":269,"cat":"その他","q":"The larger of the two conference rooms can seat forty people; ___ accommodates only fifteen.","c":["another","each other","other","the other"],"a":3,"exp":"2つのうち「もう一方」は the other。特定の2つの残り1つなので the が付く。(B)another は不特定の「別のもの」。other 系の識別は頻出。"},
{"id":270,"cat":"語彙","q":"Under his ___, the nonprofit expanded its outreach programs to twelve additional cities.","c":["leadership","led","leading","leader"],"a":0,"exp":"under one's leadership「〜の指揮の下で」が定型表現。前置詞 under の目的語となる抽象名詞 leadership。"},
{"id":271,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"All promotional materials must be approved by the legal department ___ they can be distributed to the public.","c":["after","before","once","since"],"a":1,"exp":"「配布できるようになる前に承認が必要」なので before が正解。承認→配布の順序関係を読み取る。(D)once だと「配布できるようになったら承認」で逆。"},
{"id":272,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"Were the company ___ the acquisition, its market share would nearly double overnight.","c":["complete","completing","completed","to complete"],"a":3,"exp":"Were S to do ~「仮にSが〜するなら」(仮定法未来の倒置)。If the company were to complete の倒置形。帰結節の would と呼応。上級仮定法問題。"},
{"id":273,"cat":"語彙","q":"The catering company can ___ dietary restrictions if notified at least 48 hours in advance.","c":["accommodate","tolerate","reconcile","entertain"],"a":0,"exp":"accommodate dietary restrictions「食事制限に対応する」。accommodate は「(要望に)応じる、対応する」で頻出。(B)tolerate は「我慢する」でサービス業の文脈に不適。"},
{"id":274,"cat":"品詞","q":"The orientation packet contains all the ___ necessary for completing the enrollment process.","c":["documents","document","documented","documenting"],"a":0,"exp":"all the の後ろで contains の目的語となる複数名詞 documents が正解。all the+複数名詞。necessary は後置修飾で documents necessary for ~「〜に必要な書類」。"},
{"id":275,"cat":"語彙","q":"Client files must be stored in locked cabinets to ensure ___ with data protection regulations.","c":["alliance","reliance","compliance","defiance"],"a":2,"exp":"ensure compliance with ~「〜の遵守を確実にする」が定型。(B)reliance 依存、(C)alliance 提携、(D)defiance 反抗。-ance/-iance 名詞の識別問題。"},
{"id":276,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"The gallery will be closed for installation work ___ March 3 to March 10.","c":["since","from","between","during"],"a":1,"exp":"from A to B「AからBまで」。to とペアになるのは from。(B)between は and とペア。前置詞の相関関係を問う基本問題。"},
{"id":277,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"Please remain seated until the seminar leader ___ the question-and-answer session.","c":["is opening","opens","opened","will open"],"a":1,"exp":"until が導く時の副詞節では未来のことでも現在形を使う。opens が正解。時・条件の副詞節内の現在形は最頻出の文法ルール。"},
{"id":278,"cat":"語彙","q":"The redesigned packaging is not only more attractive but also more ___ friendly.","c":["environmental","environment","environmentally","environs"],"a":2,"exp":"environmentally friendly「環境に優しい」が定型表現。friendly(形容詞)を修飾するのは副詞 environmentally。品詞と語彙の複合問題。"},
{"id":279,"cat":"品詞","q":"___ to popular belief, the museum's admission fees have not increased in over five years.","c":["Contrasting","Contrast","Contrarily","Contrary"],"a":3,"exp":"contrary to popular belief「一般に信じられているのとは逆に」が定型表現。contrary はここでは形容詞だが contrary to で前置詞的に機能する。丸ごと覚える表現。"},
{"id":280,"cat":"その他","q":"The success of the fundraising campaign exceeded ___ the organizers had originally envisioned.","c":["what","which","that","how"],"a":0,"exp":"exceeded の目的語となる先行詞込みの関係代名詞 what「〜したこと(内容)」が正解。exceed what S envisioned「想定していたものを超える」。"},
{"id":281,"cat":"語彙","q":"Volunteers will be stationed at ___ points along the marathon route to distribute water.","c":["variously","various","variable","varied widely"],"a":1,"exp":"various points「様々な地点」。名詞を修飾する various が正解。(B)variable は「変動しやすい」で意味が異なる。various/variable の識別。"},
{"id":282,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"___ the high cost of downtown office space, many startups are choosing coworking arrangements.","c":["In view of","In spite","With respect","By means"],"a":0,"exp":"in view of ~「〜を考慮して」が正解。(B)In spite は in spite of、(C)With respect は with respect to、(D)By means は by means of の形が必要。前置詞句の完全形。"},
{"id":283,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"By the end of this month, the translation team ___ over two million words for the localization project.","c":["will have processed","has processed","will process","processed"],"a":0,"exp":"By the end of this month という未来の期限までの完了なので未来完了 will have processed が正解。"},
{"id":284,"cat":"語彙","q":"The workshop fee covers all materials, ___ of the optional certification exam.","c":["exclusive","excluding that","excluded","exception"],"a":0,"exp":"exclusive of ~「〜を除いて」が定型表現。inclusive of(〜を含めて)とセットで覚える。料金の内訳説明で頻出。"},
{"id":285,"cat":"品詞","q":"Staff members responded ___ to the announcement of the profit-sharing program.","c":["enthuse","enthusiastic","enthusiastically","enthusiasm"],"a":2,"exp":"動詞 responded を修飾する副詞 enthusiastically「熱狂的に」が正解。respond enthusiastically to ~ の形。"},
{"id":286,"cat":"語彙","q":"The prototype must undergo ___ testing before it can be certified for commercial use.","c":["righteous","riotous","vigorous","rigorous"],"a":3,"exp":"rigorous testing「厳格な試験」が定型。(B)vigorous は「精力的な(運動・活動)」。rigorous/vigorous は最頻出の混同ペア。"},
{"id":287,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"Guests may store luggage at the front desk ___ no extra charge after checking out.","c":["for","at","in","with"],"a":1,"exp":"at no extra charge「追加料金なしで」が定型表現。at no cost/at no charge の at。サービス業の文脈で頻出。"},
{"id":288,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The revised safety guidelines ___ into effect as soon as the ministry grants final approval.","c":["have gone","went","going","will go"],"a":3,"exp":"as soon as 節内が現在形(grants)なので主節は未来形 will go が正解。go into effect「発効する」。時の副詞節は現在形、主節は未来形という組み合わせ。"},
{"id":289,"cat":"語彙","q":"Ms. Arden's presentation offered a ___ overview of the challenges facing the logistics industry.","c":["curtailed","brief moment","concise","shortened"],"a":2,"exp":"a concise overview「簡潔な概要」が定型コロケーション。(C)shortened は「短縮された」で元々長いものを切った意味、(D)curtailed は「削減された」。"},
{"id":290,"cat":"品詞","q":"The spa package includes a one-hour massage and ___ access to the thermal pools.","c":["unlimited","limitation","limitlessly","limit"],"a":0,"exp":"名詞 access を修飾する形容詞 unlimited「無制限の」が正解。unlimited access to ~「〜への無制限の利用」は頻出コロケーション。"},
{"id":291,"cat":"その他","q":"Ms. Vega prefers to review contract drafts ___ rather than delegate the task to junior associates.","c":["her","herself","hers","she"],"a":1,"exp":"「自分自身で」と主語を強調する再帰代名詞 herself が正解。強調用法の再帰代名詞は文末に置かれる。id:208(目的格)との対比で覚える。"},
{"id":292,"cat":"語彙","q":"The library's rare book collection is accessible ___ appointment only.","c":["with","on","through","by"],"a":3,"exp":"by appointment only「予約制のみで」が定型表現。手段の by。施設案内の頻出フレーズ。"},
{"id":293,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"___ has submitted the most innovative design will be awarded the city hall renovation contract.","c":["Whomever","Whoever","Those","Anyone"],"a":1,"exp":"名詞節を導き、節内で has submitted の主語になる Whoever「〜する人は誰でも」が正解。主語の働きなので Whomever(目的格)は不可。(C)Anyone は who が必要。"},
{"id":294,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"The shipment would have arrived on time ___ the customs inspection not taken longer than expected.","c":["had","should","were","if"],"a":0,"exp":"had the inspection not taken = if the inspection had not taken の倒置。(A)if を選ぶと if the inspection not taken となり動詞が欠ける。仮定法過去完了の倒置を見抜く上級問題。"},
{"id":295,"cat":"語彙","q":"To boost employee morale, the company introduced a ___ work schedule allowing staff to choose their start times.","c":["stretchable","elastic","flexible","adjustable perfectly"],"a":2,"exp":"flexible work schedule「フレックス勤務制度」が定型表現。勤務形態の柔軟さは flexible。(D)elastic は物理的な伸縮性。"},
{"id":296,"cat":"品詞","q":"The auditors noted a marked ___ in processing errors following the system upgrade.","c":["reduced","reduction","reducing","reduce"],"a":1,"exp":"冠詞 a+形容詞 marked の後ろなので名詞 reduction「減少」が正解。a marked reduction in ~「〜の顕著な減少」は頻出コロケーション。"},
{"id":297,"cat":"語彙","q":"Conference attendees should wear their name badges ___ at all times during the event.","c":["apparently","visibly","evidently","obviously"],"a":1,"exp":"visibly「目に見えるように」が正解。「名札を見えるように着用する」。(B)obviously/(C)apparently/(D)evidently は「明らかに、どうやら」で文修飾の副詞。"},
{"id":298,"cat":"前置詞・接続詞","q":"The restaurant sources its seafood from local fisheries ___ possible, importing only when necessary.","c":["however","whatever","whichever","whenever"],"a":3,"exp":"whenever possible「可能な限り(いつでも)」が定型表現。「可能なときは地元産、必要時のみ輸入」という文意。"},
{"id":299,"cat":"動詞の形","q":"Management anticipates ___ the vacant positions by the end of the recruiting season.","c":["fill","filled","filling","to fill"],"a":2,"exp":"anticipate は動名詞を目的語に取る動詞。anticipate filling「埋めることを見込む」。anticipate/consider/suggest/avoid+動名詞のグループ。"},
{"id":300,"cat":"語彙","q":"The board meeting has been moved to the annex, ___ construction noise in the main building.","c":["since that","because","owing to","for that"],"a":2,"exp":"後ろが名詞句 construction noise なので前置詞 owing to「〜のせいで」が正解。(B)because は接続詞。理由を表す前置詞句(due to/owing to/because of)の使い分け。"}
];
